Intraspecific variation.
The outer distal corner of maxilliped basis can vary in how much it is produced; pereopod-1 having posterior margin of propodus with four or five ventral spiniform setae and can vary in number of setae on ischium, from few to many (
Fig. 5D, E
); the fixed finger of the male cheliped usually has three proximal teeth but can have four, two (
Fig. 10C
), or one, a large distal tooth can be present with several spinules between it and nail, the ventral margin can have four simple setae; number of articles of antennae and number of setae on squama can slightly vary depending on developmental stage.
